  "observations": [
    "3-tier hierarchical browse tree (catalog → schema → object-type → object) as primary navigation, resizable split-pane",
    "Master-detail shell: tree on left, detail tabs on right, persisted across navigation",
    "Polymorphic securable: Table/View/Volume/Function/Model/AITool share unified detail tabs (Overview/Permissions/Lineage/History) with type-specific tabs added (Sample Data for Table, Files for Volume, Versions for Model)",
    "Hero identity uses fully-qualified path catalog.schema.object as canonical id with copy-to-clipboard",
    "Type badge + format badge differentiate Managed/External/Foreign/Streaming and Delta/Iceberg/Parquet at hero level",
    "Quick-action toolbar above tabs: Open in Notebook / Query in SQL Editor / Sample / Refresh — context-shaped CTAs",
    "Sample Data tab auto-fetches first N rows lazy on tab activation, cached per session",
    "Permissions tab as principal × privilege grid (matrix) rather than list — both axes browsable",
    "History tab as version timeline with operation-typed rows (Delta time-travel as first-class)",
    "Lineage tab as graph canvas with toggle for column-level vs table-level granularity, upstream/downstream split",
    "Quality and Insights tabs surface derived/passive metadata alongside structural metadata — same tab strip",
    "Tags rendered as chip cluster, key:value pairs, attachable to schema/table/column polymorphically",
    "Classification labels visually distinct from tags (sensitivity tier coloring) and drive automatic masking policies",
    "Column tree in Overview shows nullable, type, comment, tags, classification inline — dense table",
    "Search bar global across catalogs/schemas/tables with type-grouped autocomplete",
    "Filter chips toolbar (tag, owner, type) above tree for cross-cutting filtering",
    "Foreign catalog visually marked in tree (federation icon) but treated as first-class — uniform detail surface",
    "Delta Sharing surfaced as separate top-level area: Shares (out-bound) + Recipients (counterparties) — outside main tree",
    "Volume browse as file-tree (nested directories) inside detail tab — Volume = securable wrapper around hierarchical files",
    "Permissions inheritance visualized: catalog-level grants shown as inherited rows on schema/table permission tabs",
    "Service principals and groups rendered in same picker as users — first-class principals",
    "Row filters / column masks defined as references to UDF (Function entity) — composition over inline expressions",
    "ABAC policies separate top-level area; their effect propagates to permission tab as derived row-filter badge on affected tables",
    "Audit log accessible both as system table query AND as per-resource activity tab — dual surface",
    "Genie integration: NL prompt input above tree/results, generated SQL shown as preview before execute, permissions enforced at exec time",
    "Notebook integration: schema browser as side panel inside notebook editor reuses same tree primitive as Catalog Explorer",
    "Time-travel query via History tab → 'Query at version N' CTA opens SQL editor pre-populated",
    "Drop with cascade dialog requires type-to-confirm and lists impacted children",
    "Transfer ownership flagged as high-irreversibility — full form with current+new owner + reason field",
    "Model detail surfaces Versions list + Aliases (champion/challenger) as separate panels; aliases reassignable via inline action",
    "Serving endpoint state (pending/ready/updating/failed) shown with traffic-light badge on model detail",
    "AI Tool detail emphasizes LLM-readable description field — distinct treatment from Function comment"
  ]
}